         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/7/65 ¶ Dear Dr Hooker. ¶ The consignment of Cereus, Dahlias, etc, which you were so kind to transmit by last mail arrived and while I have to express to you my gratitude for your generosity I am gl...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.07.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70. f. 171.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/7/65</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Hooker.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The consignment of <name key="Cereus">Cereus</name>, <name key="Dahlia">Dahlia</name>s, etc, which you were so kind to transmit by last mail arrived and while I have to express to you my gratitude for your generosity I am glad to say that the majority of the plants arrived in safety and are mostly new to this garden.</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The consignment was sent from Kew on 17 May 1865 (RBG Kew, Library (Kewensia), Outward Book, 1860-69, p. 234). The box contained 34 plants, including 11 varieties of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <name key="Dahlia">Dahlia</name>
                        </seg> and five species of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <name key="Cereus">Cereus</name>
                        </seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> I was glad to learn, that your venerable father had recovered from his late attack of Bronchitis and trust you will not allow any exposure of his to the inclemency of the weather, which might bring on new attacks. It would be a dreadful loss to all of us, if he was suddenly carried away.</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg style="">See J. Hooker to M, 2 May 1865.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have always hoped that he would be a Cententarian &amp; that he would see yet much of the results of his labours turned to account by others</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I feel obliged for the spikes of the Tussoc Grass, and trust to make them grow. The plant would evidently be a great acquisition if not here at least in the colder parts of New Zealand &amp; in the Chatham Islands. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sorry you had so much trouble about getting the life plants, especially as the exertions proved vain. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will attend to your wish for having terrestrial Orchids for your Garden[.]</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg style="">See J. Hooker to M, 2 May 1865.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>About two years ago I sent a specimen of a grass for Colonel Munro's inspection. Your worthy friend pronounced it a new section of <name key="Panicum">Panicum</name>. On examination I find, that it is <name key="Neurachne%20Mitchelliana">Neurachne Mitchelliana</name>, though I have no authentic specimen for comparison. It is possible that <name key="Neurachne%20paradoxa">Neurachne paradoxa</name>, of which I have abundant specimens as well as N. montana, which I know only from Gaudichauds figure</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg style="">Freycinet (1826), pl. 26.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> as well as the Darling Grass are all species of different genera. The caryopsis of <name key="Neurachne%20paradoxa">Neurachne paradoxa</name> is very large.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">The escallonious genus <name key="Cuttsia">Cuttsia</name> is worthy of your attention for the genera plantarum</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg style="">M erected </seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <name key="Cuttsia">Cuttsia</name>
                        </seg>
                        <seg style=""> (</seg>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">C. viburnea</seg>
                        <seg style="">) in B65.07.03, p. 47.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cereus">Cereus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cuttsia">Cuttsia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dahlia">Dahlia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Neurachne%20Mitchelliana">Neurachne Mitchelliana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Neurachne%20montana">Neurachne montana</name>,</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Neurachne%20paradoxa">Neurachne paradoxa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Panicum">Panicum</name>
            </p>
